<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <%- include('partials/head', { title }) %>
  <body>
    <%- include('partials/site-header') %>

    <main class="page">
      <div class="layout-narrow">
        <article>
          <header class="page-intro">
            <h1>About me</h1>
          </header>

          <figure class="article-hero">
            <img src="/assets/author.svg" alt="Portrait of Admin" width="1200" height="600" />
            <figcaption>Admin</figcaption>
          </figure>

          <div class="article-body">
            <p>
              Welcome to <strong>My Blog</strong> — a small personal site for short
              posts about technology, food, travel, and everyday ideas.
            </p>
            <p>
              The blog is intentionally simple. It runs on Node.js with server-side
              rendering and a SQLite database — a place to write things down and
              share them.
            </p>
            <h2>What you&rsquo;ll find here</h2>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Travel</strong> — trips, places, and getting around.</li>
              <li><strong>Tech</strong> — notes on building simple, useful software.</li>
              <li><strong>Food</strong> — easy recipes and kitchen ideas.</li>
              <li><strong>Life</strong> — everyday thoughts and updates.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              Want to say hello or suggest a topic? The
              <a href="/contact">contact page</a> is the best way to reach me.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </main>

    <%- include('partials/footer') %>
  </body>
</html>
